sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS successful_access_count
FROM system_access
WHERE user_id = 1 AND is_successful = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS successful_logins
FROM login_logs
WHERE user_id = 1 AND is_successful = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'Introduction to Anthropology' is a specific course; 
- A user's full name is composed of their first name and last name;
- 'Total activity duration' refers to the sum of the duration of all activities on a specific course.

- 'Most active users' refers to users with the highest activity counts; 
- 'Activity count' refers to the number of activities a user has performed in the system; 
- 'Login count' refers to the number of times a user has logged in to the system.

sql:
SELECT user_id
FROM users
ORDER BY user_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'top 3 users' refers to the users with the highest rank based on the number of logins and total login duration; 
- 'past month' refers to the last 30 days.
- 'longest total login time' means the users who have spent the most time logged in.

